If you only need the numbers, `get_risk_table_frame()` returns them as a tidy frame, which you can
render however you like, including through Great Tables. It is backend-neutral, so it works whether
or not you have a plotting library installed.

::: {#a12c1090 .cell execution_count=10}
``` {.python .cell-code}
# Return the risk counts as a tidy DataFrame (backend-neutral, no plotting required)
gw.get_risk_table_frame(km, times=[0, 250, 500, 750, 1000], format="polars")
