## Customizing the plot

The `plot_survival()` function returns an ordinary Altair chart, so you refine it with Altair's API.
Chaining `.properties()` sets the title and dimensions, and you can keep layering or restyling from
there.

::: {#4ba4e2ea .cell execution_count=12}
``` {.python .cell-code}
# Refine the chart with Altair's .properties() — title and dimensions
gw.plot_survival(km).properties(
    title="Survival by sex", width=640, height=360
)
```

