Hazard ratios below 1 indicate a reduced hazard relative to the reference (e.g. sex = 2, female, has
a lower hazard than male), and the position of the CI relative to the reference line shows whether
the effect is statistically distinguishable from zero at the chosen confidence level. The tooltip on
each row shows the formatted "HR (lower–upper)" text and the p-value.

### Renaming terms for display

Column names from the data often need to be rewritten for a publication figure. Pass `term_labels=`
as a dict mapping internal names to display labels. Only the terms you list are renamed. The rest
keep their original names.

::: {#262e6abd .cell execution_count=14}
``` {.python .cell-code}
# Rename internal covariate labels to publication-friendly display strings
gw.plot_forest(
    cox,
    term_labels={
        "age": "Age (years)",
        "sex": "Female vs. Male",
        "ph.ecog": "ECOG PS (0–4)",
    },
    title="Cox model: NCCTG Lung Cancer",
)
```

