### Customizing the plot

The `plot_cif()` function returns an Altair chart object, so it composes with the rest of the Altair
grammar. The most common adjustments are available directly as keyword arguments:

::: {#58e0d5e9 .cell execution_count=22}
``` {.python .cell-code}
# Suppress the confidence band (conf_int=False) and tighten the panel dimensions
gw.plot_cif(
    aj_sex,
    conf_int=False,   # hide the shaded CI band for a cleaner comparison
    width=350,        # width of each cause panel in pixels
    height=250,       # height of each cause panel in pixels
)
```

